content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 22.33 - Responsibility of dealers and the reclassification of milk

State Regulations
(a) All pool milk shall be class I milk
unless the dealer who first received such milk, including that moved to another
plant, satisfies the commissioner that such milk should be classified
otherwise. (b) Any pool milk shall
be reclassified if verification by the commissioner discloses that the original
classification was incorrect. Notes
